article.headline: James Madison 53, UMBC 51
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Julius Wells scored 18 points and James Madison defeated Maryland-Baltimore County 53-51 on Saturday night. Wells shot 7-for-15 from the field, including four 3-pointers for the Dukes (3-2). James Madison led 45-43 with 8 minutes to play when they went on a 7-0 run. Two free throws from Desmond Thornton made the score 52-43 with 2:29 remaining. The Retrievers responded with an 8-0 run, and a jumper by Robbie Jackson cut the lead to 52-51 with 33 seconds left. The Dukes made only 1 of 3 free throws in their final two possessions, but the Retrievers failed to capitalize, missing two jumpers to end the game. UMBC (0-5) was led by Jackson, who scored 12 points and grabbed seven rebounds. The Retrievers outrebounded James Madison 41-32, but shot only 31 percent from the field (18-for-58).
